00:04:58.300 --> 00:05:02.010
filters into their real life,
so risk to their health,

00:05:02.010 --> 00:05:05.750
risk to their relationships,
risk to their house,

00:05:05.750 --> 00:05:07.730
their mortgage.

00:05:07.730 --> 00:05:11.230
So, , again, we start from
a fairly curious place.

00:05:11.230 --> 00:05:13.720
These are people who
deliberately invite risk

00:05:13.720 --> 00:05:15.940
into their lives.

00:05:15.940 --> 00:05:17.890
So here's the bit
about resilience.

00:05:17.890 --> 00:05:21.270
And I'm often asked,
what is it that I

00:05:21.270 --> 00:05:24.820
look for when I make an
angel investment or any kind

00:05:24.820 --> 00:05:25.550
of investment.

00:05:25.550 --> 00:05:29.200
And it is always-- if I had to
pick one characteristic that I

00:05:29.200 --> 00:05:30.710
always look for in
the entrepreneurs

00:05:30.710 --> 00:05:34.440
that I back, it
would be resilience.

00:05:34.440 --> 00:05:37.250
And so what do I mean by that?

00:05:37.250 --> 00:05:41.490
There are two ways of thinking
about resilience in my book.

00:05:41.490 --> 00:05:46.590
One is around protecting the
downside of entrepreneurship

00:05:46.590 --> 00:05:47.820
or innovation.

00:05:47.820 --> 00:05:50.510
And another is
unlocking the upside.

00:05:50.510 --> 00:05:54.100
So starting with
protecting the downside,

00:05:54.100 --> 00:05:58.330
I think resilience
for me is the ability

00:05:58.330 --> 00:06:00.920
to manage stress and anxiety.

00:06:00.920 --> 00:06:03.201
You will be told,
as an innovator

00:06:03.201 --> 00:06:04.700
in a big company
or an entrepreneur,

00:06:04.700 --> 00:06:06.350
you'll be told no 1,000 times.

00:06:06.350 --> 00:06:07.336
That's a stupid idea.

00:06:07.336 --> 00:06:08.210
Get out of my office.

00:06:08.210 --> 00:06:09.540
That can't be done.

00:06:09.540 --> 00:06:11.690
So how do you pick
yourself up from that?

00:06:11.690 --> 00:06:16.530
It tends to be a fairly
anxiety-inducing environment.

00:06:16.530 --> 00:06:19.640
So how do you manage your
own stress and anxiety

00:06:19.640 --> 00:06:22.530
within a situation like that?

00:06:22.530 --> 00:06:25.200
The second aspect
of it is the ability

00:06:25.200 --> 00:06:28.900
to make decisions in
highly ambiguous, highly

00:06:28.900 --> 00:06:32.120
uncertain, highly
volatile situations.

00:06:32.120 --> 00:06:34.520
That's what all of you
do when you're being

00:06:34.520 --> 00:06:36.280
innovative in a big company.

00:06:36.280 --> 00:06:37.930
It's what entrepreneurs
do when they're

00:06:37.930 --> 00:06:40.600
being innovative in
a startup context.

00:06:40.600 --> 00:06:42.890
So that's the protecting
the downside bit.

00:06:42.890 --> 00:06:46.390
Those are the characteristics
of resilience that we look for.

00:06:46.390 --> 00:06:49.200
And then in terms of
unlocking the upside,

00:06:49.200 --> 00:06:50.460
let me ask a question.

00:06:50.460 --> 00:06:55.820
Who can tell me the
opposite of fragile?

00:06:55.820 --> 00:06:58.620
What's the opposite of fragile?

00:06:58.620 --> 00:07:00.312
Any words or phrases
spring to mind?

