00:07:13.000 --> 00:07:17.550
And so in a way, though,
robust and strong--

00:07:17.550 --> 00:07:21.920
if fragile is falls over when
risk or volatility, uncertainty

00:07:21.920 --> 00:07:25.130
comes along, strong
and robust just means

00:07:25.130 --> 00:07:29.730
can withstand uncertainty,
volatility, risk.

00:07:29.730 --> 00:07:33.050
And Nassim Taleb, who wrote
"The Black Swan," which I think

00:07:33.050 --> 00:07:34.960
is an amazing book,
wrote another book

00:07:34.960 --> 00:07:37.950
called "Antrifragile"
because he said

00:07:37.950 --> 00:07:41.110
there isn't a word for
the opposite of fragile.

00:07:41.110 --> 00:07:44.640
In the sense that what is it--
and he describes innovators

00:07:44.640 --> 00:07:46.710
and entrepreneurs in
this way-- what is it

00:07:46.710 --> 00:07:50.140
that not just can
withstand risk, volatility,

00:07:50.140 --> 00:07:55.010
and uncertainty, but positively
blossoms and flourishes

00:07:55.010 --> 00:07:56.350
with more risk?

00:07:56.350 --> 00:07:58.760
And again, that's a
pretty unusual concept.

00:07:58.760 --> 00:08:03.187
And he said entrepreneurs,
innovators are such people.

00:08:03.187 --> 00:08:05.520
And the way he describes it,
I think it's really, really

00:08:05.520 --> 00:08:09.250
powerful-- very, very
interesting-- is innovators,

00:08:09.250 --> 00:08:12.490
entrepreneurs are--
they open themselves

00:08:12.490 --> 00:08:17.460
up to risk and
uncertainty because risk

00:08:17.460 --> 00:08:19.390
is information rich.

00:08:19.390 --> 00:08:22.130
It's rich in information
about your competitors,

00:08:22.130 --> 00:08:25.220
about your customers,
about your investors.

00:08:25.220 --> 00:08:29.180
So if you open yourself
up to it, yes, it's scary.

00:08:29.180 --> 00:08:32.067
But actually, it means
that you're nimble.

00:08:32.067 --> 00:08:32.900
You're on your feet.

00:08:32.900 --> 00:08:34.510
You're getting all
the information

00:08:34.510 --> 00:08:35.929
about the marketplace.

00:08:35.929 --> 00:08:39.090
So risk is information
rich, I think,

00:08:39.090 --> 00:08:40.970
is an incredibly
powerful insight.

00:08:40.970 --> 00:08:45.576
And for me, it helps explain why
entrepreneurs do what they do,

00:08:45.576 --> 00:08:46.700
innovators do what they do.

00:08:46.700 --> 00:08:49.550
They open themselves up to risk.

00:08:49.550 --> 00:08:53.780
So that's how I often
think about resilience.

00:08:53.780 --> 00:08:58.050
That's what I look for in the
entrepreneurs that I back.

